Usage: ./mailseek [options] [files]
Options:
  --no-recursive   Do not dive into directories, default is recursive
  --case           Case sensitive match, default is case insensitive
  --any            Succeed if any criterium matches, by default all criteria
                   must match
  --verbose        Provide verbose output on STDERR
  --debug          Provide debug output on STDERR
  --null           Separate file names by NUL chars, default is newline
  --details        Print some headers, not only the file name
Filter options:
  --newer DATETIME, --older DATETIME        Filter by date and time
  --filetime               Date-time filtering is based on file's time, not
                           on Email's Date header (faster)
  --sender PATTERN         From, Sender, Originator, Return-Path headers
  --recipient PATTERN      To, Cc, Bcc, Delivered-To headers
  --subject PATTERN        The Subject header
  --attachment PATTERN     Search in name of attachments (Email parts)
  --mime PATTERN/PATTERN   MIME type (type/subtype) of Email parts
  --header NAME:PATTERN    Search in the named header
  --body QUERY             Body text (plain text and html are supported)
Formats:
  DATETIME    "YYYY-mm-dd_HH:MM:SS" - meant in current time zone
              You can omit any elements only from the right
  PATTERN     a) simple string - match case insensitive substring
              b) "~REGEX" - match as regexp if PATTERN starts with tilde
              PATTERN is optionally prefixed by '!' which inverts filtering
  QUERY       Fulltext search expression, see Search::Fulltext(3pm)
